<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[174,1128,189,283]" lastBlockId="9.[174,1126,189,283]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
The original range of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[504,640,190,216]" class="Arachnida" family="Sicariidae" genus="Loxosceles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[504,640,190,216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">L. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the circum-Mediterranean region. However, due to human activity, it is now distributed in Southern Europe and Northern Africa to 
<collectingCountry box="[478,529,257,283]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Iran</collectingCountry>
and introduced in 
<collectingCountry box="[779,840,257,283]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">USA</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[855,948,257,283]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Macaronesia, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,297,189,215]" name="South Africa" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[312,379,189,215]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[394,471,189,215]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[486,559,190,216]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[574,651,190,216]" name="South Korea" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[665,726,190,216]" name="Laos" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[741,855,189,215]" name="Thailand" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[868,984,189,215]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Australia</collectingCountry>
, Hawaii (
<bibRefCitation author="GERTSCH, W. J. &amp; ENNIK F." box="[145,425,223,250]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="264 - 360" refId="ref4372" refString="GERTSCH, W. J. &amp; ENNIK F. (1983): The spider genus Loxosceles in North America, Central America, and the West Indies (Araneae, Loxoscelidae). - Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 175: 264 - 360." type="journal article" year="1983">GERTSCH &amp; ENNIK 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="HARVEY, M. S." box="[434,596,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="223 - 224" refId="ref4678" refString="HARVEY, M. S. (1996): The first record of the Fiddle-back spider Loxisceles rufescens (Araneae: Sicariidae) from Western Australia. - Records of the Western Australian Museum 18: 223 - 224." type="journal article" year="1996">HARVEY 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="MIRSHAMSI, O. &amp; HATAMI, M. &amp; ZAMANI, A." box="[605,866,223,250]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="83 - 86" refId="ref5129" refString="MIRSHAMSI, O., HATAMI, M. &amp; ZAMANI, A. (2013): New record of the Mediterranean recluse spider Loxosceles rufescens (Dufour, 1820) and its bite from Khorasan Province, northeast of Iran (Aranei: Sicariidae). - Iranian Journal of Animal Biosystematics 9: 83 - 86." type="journal article" year="2013">
MIRSHAMSI 
<emphasis box="[747,794,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="CHOMPHUPHUANG, N. &amp; DEOWANISH, S. &amp; SONGSANGCHOTE, C. &amp; SIVAYYAPRAM, V. &amp; THONGPREM, P. &amp; WARRIT, N." pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="142 - 147" refId="ref4049" refString="CHOMPHUPHUANG, N., DEOWANISH, S., SONGSANGCHOTE, C., SIVAYYAPRAM, V., THONGPREM, P. &amp; WARRIT, N. (2016): The Mediterranean recluse spider Loxosceles rufescens (Dufour, 1820) (Araneae: Sicariidae) established in a natural cave in Thailand. - Journal of Arachnology 44: 142 - 147. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / R 15 - 61" type="journal article" year="2016">
CHOMPHUPHUANG 
<emphasis box="[136,183,257,283]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="TRIVEDI, V. &amp; DAL, P." box="[265,510,257,283]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref5966" refString="TRIVEDI, V. &amp; DAL, P. (2019): Occurrence, distribution and description of Loxosceles rufescens (Dufour, 1820) (Araneae: Sicariidae) from western India. - Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society 116: 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.17087 / jbnhs / 2019 / v 116 / 123017" type="journal article" year="2019">TRIVEDI &amp; DAL 2019</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="WSC" box="[520,650,257,283]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" refId="ref6032" refString="WSC (2020): World Spider Catalog. Version 20.0. Natural History Museum Bern, online at http: // wsc. nmbe. ch [accessed on 20.08.2020] https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="url" year="2020">WSC 2020</bibRefCitation>
). For the Balkans it is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[135,226,290,316]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="GRBAC, I. &amp; KATUSIC, L. &amp; LUKIC, M." box="[246,463,290,316]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="185 - 269" refId="ref4422" refString="GRBAC, I., KATUSIC, L. &amp; LUKIC, M. (2019): Catalogue of spiders (Araneae) deposited in the Croatian Natural History Museum, Zagreb. - Natura Croatica 28: 185 - 269. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2019.28.19" type="journal article" year="2019">
GRBAC 
<emphasis box="[335,392,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
), European 
<collectingCountry box="[614,702,290,316]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="YIGIT, N. &amp; BAYRAM, A. &amp; ULASOGLU, D. &amp; DANISMAN, T. &amp; CORAC OCAL, I. &amp; SANCAK, Z." box="[718,916,290,318]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" pagination="178 - 187" refId="ref6074" refString="YIGIT, N., BAYRAM, A., ULASOGLU, D., DANISMAN, T., CORAC OCAL, I. &amp; SANCAK, Z. (2008): Loxosceles spider bite in Turkey (Loxosceles rufescens, Sicariidae, Araneae). - Journal of Venomous Animals and Toxins including Tropical Diseases 14: 178 - 187. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1678 - 91992008000100016" type="journal article" year="2008">
YIĞIT 
<emphasis box="[792,849,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="DANISMAN, T. &amp; KUNT, K. B. &amp; OZKUTUK, R. S." lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" refId="ref4259" refString="DANISMAN, T., KUNT, K. B. &amp; OZKUTUK, R. S. (2019): The checklist of the spiders of Turkey. - [Internet] Version 2019. Online at http: // www. spidersofturkey. info [accessed on 20.08.2020]" type="url" year="2019">
DANIŞMAN 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[345,430,190,216]" name="Greece" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Greece</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BOSMANS, R. &amp; CHATZAKI, M." box="[449,790,189,216]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref3932" refString="BOSMANS, R. &amp; CHATZAKI, M. (2005): A catalogue of the spiders of Greece. - Newsletter of the Belgian Arachnological Society 20: 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="2005">BOSMANS &amp; CHATZAKI 2005</bibRefCitation>
, RUSSELL- 
<bibRefCitation author="SMITH, A. &amp; ALLISON, R. &amp; ASKINS, M. &amp; BLUMSOM, W. &amp; SNAZELL, R. &amp; SPILLING, C." box="[911,1122,189,216]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72" pagination="133 - 167" refId="ref5715" refString="RUSSELL- SMITH, A., ALLISON, R., ASKINS, M., BLUMSOM, W., SNAZELL, R. &amp; SPILLING, C. (2011): A provisional checklist and gazetteer of the spiders of Chios, Greece (Arachnida: Araneae). - Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society 15: 133 - 167. https: // doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2010.15.5.133" type="journal article" year="2011">
SMITH 
<emphasis box="[995,1046,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="BOSMANS, R. &amp; VAN KEER, J. &amp; SMITH, A. &amp; KRONESTEDT, T. &amp; ALDERWEIRELDT, M. &amp; LAERS, J. &amp; KONINCK &amp; DE H." box="[174,416,223,250]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72" pagination="1 - 147" refId="ref3966" refString="BOSMANS, R., VAN KEER, J., RUSSELL- SMITH, A., KRONESTEDT, T. ALDERWEIRELDT, M., BOSSE- LAERS, J. &amp; KONINCK, DE H. (2013): Spiders of Crete (Araneae). A catalogue of all currently known species from the Greek island of Crete. Arachnological Contributions. - Newsletter of the Belgian Arachnological Society 28 (Suppl. 1): 1 - 147." type="journal article" year="2013">
BOSMANS 
<emphasis box="[293,341,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
), including Kerkyra (Corfu) 
<collectingCountry box="[771,848,223,249]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Island</collectingCountry>
(RUSSELL- 
<bibRefCitation author="SMITH, A." box="[972,1114,223,249]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72" pagination="285 - 300" refId="ref5665" refString="RUSSELL- SMITH, A. (2014): Spiders from the Ionian islands of Kerkyra (Corfu) and Lefkada, Greece (Arachnida: Aranei). - Arthropoda Selecta 23: 285 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / arthsel. 23.3.08" type="journal article" year="2014">SMITH 2014</bibRefCitation>
), so finding it in Saranda was not surprising.
</paragraph>
